* [range]global/{pattern}/[cmd] command allows us to execute an ex command for every line that matches the pattern
* [range]vglobal/{pattern}/[cmd] command allows us to execute an ex command for every line that does not match the given pattern
* We can save our complex ex commands in a file and then we can use it on multiple files all we need to do populate the file with series of ex commands seperated with line breaks
* We can use our vim script on multiple files
* :source command allows us to execute the vim script
* We can open multiple files with vim. We can see the each opened file with the ":args" command
* We can go to a next file using ":next" command ":previous" does the opposite of the ":next" command
* We can use ":argdo" command the execute an ex command on series of files
